0) Simple Conversion Management

- Simply check each conversion without any flags'cspdiuxX%'
- Try special case like 0 or smallest int or empty string or null pointer
- Try with multiple arguments/conversions
- Try the various conversions in the middle of a sentence (with other characters before and/or after)


1) nfge

- Check if conversion n f g e are working fine (beware of n) with all the flags combination
- Each working conversion  give 1
- If all conversions are working give a bonus 1


2) Simple Flags Management

- Use the 's' conversion for all the following test
- Check minimum field width bigger, equal and smaller than the string
- Check minimum field width bigger, equal and smaller than the string with -
- Check minimum field width bigger, equal and smaller than the string with 0
- Check '.' with multiple precisions


3) l ll h hh

- Check all the conversions with l ll h hh with all the other flags combination
- Each working flag give 1
- If all flags are working give a bonus 1


4) \# '+

- Check all the conversions with \# ' + and space with all the other flags combination
- Each working flag give 1
- If all flags are working give a bonus 1


5) Advanced Flags Management

- Use the 's' conversion for all the following test
- Check '*' as minimum field width (try values like negative one, zero etc.)
- Check '*' as precision (try values like negative one, zero etc.)
- Check '*' as both with/without one other flag (try values like negative one, zero etc.)


6) Get Crazy

- Try any combination flags and conversions
- Check what happen with duplicate flags


